==English==
===Etymology===
From [[Setswana]] A public place where consultation and judicial proceedings are conducted.
===Noun===
'''lekgotla'''
# A consultative process between groups persuing a common goal.
*2001. Media briefing by President Thabo Mbeki: 'Cabinet held its second '''lekgotla''' for the year on 23-25 July 2001. The mid-year meeting was aimed at reviewing the implementation of the programme government announced at the beginning of the year'. 


*
===Translations===
*Bemba - insala
*Shona - dare
*Zulu - inkundla.
